Czech Firms’ Owners Get $55 Bln in Dividends, HN Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-02-11T08:25:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/czech-firms-owners-get-55-bln-in-dividends-hn-says-correct-.html
(Corrects headline, first paragraph to show size of
dividends was in trillions of koruna.)  International companies with Czech
subsidiaries, such as Erste Group Bank AG and KBC Groep NV, have
received more than 1 trillion koruna ($55 billion) in dividends
since 2000,  Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing data from the
Czech National Bank.  The figure doesn’t include the final quarter of 2010, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  